name: Ritchie Tiongson
text: If you have time to spare, it doesn't hurt. I found it to be an interesting read, great setting, good plot, decent dialogue... but it's also a book whose presentation I didn't like to much, and where I found the supporting cast to be more interesting than the main protagonist. Overall, good, but not great, read.
